      "part_type": "Hadith",
      "path": "/books/man-la-yahduruhu-al-faqih:2:3:136:11",
      "source_url": "https://thaqalayn.net/hadith/34/3/136/11",
      "text": [
        " «اَلْقَانِعُ هُوَ اَلَّذِي يَقْنَعُ بِمَا تُعْطِيهِ وَ اَلْمُعْتَرُّ اَلَّذِي يَعْتَرِيكَ »."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.3053 - Imam Jafar ibn Muhammad Al-Sadiq (as) was asked about the words of Allah (swt), the Exalted: \"Then when they are down on their sides (after being sacrificed), eat from them and feed the contented one and the beggar.\" (Surah Al-Hajj 22:36)\nImam (as) replied: \"The 'contented one' is the one who accepts whatever you give him, and the 'beggar' is the one who approaches you asking.\""
        ]
      }
    },
